45:54.780 --> 46:05.780
And the reason is very simple. Because the tall whites, like the teacher, can tell what a person is thinking, even if they're not talking.

46:05.780 --> 46:19.780
Well, if you're debriefed and they're very touchy about their children, if a briefing person were to say, what kind of mother is the teacher?

46:19.780 --> 46:26.780
You know, how does she treat her little girl? I mean, she was lost in the sagebrush and you saved her life. How did they let that happen?

46:26.780 --> 46:35.780
See, then they wouldn't have to ask me to tell them about it. See, they could tell it by just reading my thoughts.

46:35.780 --> 46:47.780
The next thing they would demand is that somebody, like that officer, be delivered to them out in the desert, and he wouldn't live another moment, okay?

46:47.780 --> 46:55.780
Yeah. And I wouldn't have to say anything or do anything or say else, because she could just tell, oh yeah, I read Charlie and I see that happened.

46:55.780 --> 47:03.780
So when I say that no one could ever ask me questions, I could never be debriefed. Nothing I would do would ever be classified.

47:03.780 --> 47:16.780
I mean, they couldn't even inspect me. If they wanted to talk to me, they physically had to come out to the parking out of the chow hall at Indian Springs between noon and 1230.

47:16.780 --> 47:25.780
And I would meet them there if I felt like meeting them, or if I didn't, then they would just, and before they went out, they would have to check in with the base commander at Nellis.

47:25.780 --> 47:38.780
And when they came back, they had to go directly from checking on base to the base commander and say, yeah, I looked healthy and so on. And I could, and they couldn't come out and inspect my barracks or see anything.

47:38.780 --> 47:54.520
Have you, you mentioned the CIA psychiatrist who said that you had all these psychological defenses and that sort of allowed you to enter into relations with the ETs and come back in time.

47:54.520 --> 48:07.480
So it allowed me to protect my thoughts, the person I am, before admitting to myself, they are real and I know what I'm going to do.

48:07.680 --> 48:11.260
Have you ever heard the name Kit Green? Is that familiar to you at all?

48:11.260 --> 48:37.500
Hmm. It doesn't ring a bell, but I probably heard them. But see, like, see, like, like the first thing I agreed, the first agreement I made with them was after realizing they were real, that I asked them that whenever they came around me, that they talk between themselves, if they were talking between themselves or with me in a way that I could hear to speak English,

48:37.500 --> 49:03.200
because it frightened me if they were talking between themselves. And it sometimes sounded like horse winnings or bird calls. And they agreed. And then the second one was that if I saw them out in the desert, like if I came over a rise and there was one sitting on a rock, I understood that it was easy for me to sneak up on them behind them and surprise them. And I didn't want to do that.

49:03.200 --> 49:23.760
And I would just stop where I was and stand where I was and sing a song and let them know I was there. And then if they wanted to come closer, I would just stand there and they could walk up towards me and stop whenever they wanted to.

49:23.760 --> 49:45.500
I wouldn't pursue, I wouldn't pursue, I wouldn't close the gap. And if they got too close to me so that it, I started feeling intimidated, I would start backing away and they would stop. And then when we had decided how far apart we were going to be physically, then we could communicate.

49:46.140 --> 49:51.700
Your wife, Marie-Therese, mentioned that you actually were sent out initially.

49:51.700 --> 50:19.620
Initially, I was supposed to go from, after doing my basic training at Lackland, then I was put in PAT standing. You know, that was airmen waiting their security clearance. Okay. And those airmen that were going to get a security clearance and be sent to San Angeles, Texas for security school 101, were supposed to wait there for like three weeks or so. Okay.

50:19.620 --> 50:29.980
Now, the security clearance you're waiting for is whatever the government decides to give you, but it's supposed to be the top secret clearance. Okay.

50:29.980 --> 50:45.260
Now, the security, the security training, the people who are sent to San Angeles, Texas are waiting to get their orders to San Angeles, Texas.

50:45.260 --> 50:59.500
However, in my case, they've issued two sets of orders, the real ones to San Angeles, Texas, and the cover orders to the weather training school at Shunard Air Force Base, Illinois.

50:59.500 --> 51:15.700
The idea is that the captain, who is in charge of those guys, who has a safe for classified material that's locked, this is 1965, times have all changed since then, he's the one that will give out my orders.

51:15.700 --> 51:27.920
Yes. The day sergeant can give out all the rest of the orders. Okay. Yeah. Because the day sergeant, because my clearance is going to be a higher clearance than theirs.

51:27.920 --> 51:42.880
Well, the Friday that they came in, the captain is off playing golf. Now, as a military officer, he's supposed to be on duty. He's off playing golf and left the sergeant in command.

51:42.880 --> 51:58.840
The sergeant does not have the clearance to know about my orders. So, when the orders come in for everybody else, and we were all in the same class together at boot camp, I think a mistake has been made.

51:59.680 --> 52:11.280
Okay. They get their orders. I go in with them. There's no orders. I say, well, because my cover orders are in a different location than their orders,

52:11.280 --> 52:22.700
but they're not locked up, see? They're just in the temporary outbox. Well, I asked the sergeant, I got no orders. I go into weather school, too.

52:22.700 --> 52:28.900
So, the sergeant goes and gets those orders and says, oh, yeah, here's your orders, and hands them to me to go to weather training school.

52:28.980 --> 52:35.880
So, I go out and I get on the bus. You know, I got my stuff back. Now, my drill sergeant had made a very special point.

52:35.940 --> 52:40.980
He said, anytime you do anything in the military, keep two copies of your orders because you can't trust your officers.

52:41.860 --> 52:50.440
Right? Genius, right? I keep two copies, right? Okay. So, I get on the bus. I'm not in the travel mass, but I got orders.

52:50.580 --> 52:54.760
So, what? So, they throw me on the airplane, and they send me to shoot at Air Force Base, Illinois.

52:55.020 --> 53:01.960
If you can't shoot them, shinoot them, that place. Okay. Well, I'm in the base, and everybody else is getting paid,

53:01.960 --> 53:08.420
and I'm at weather school, and I'm the best student in the class. And after, like, six weeks, I still haven't been paid.

53:08.420 --> 53:16.220
And so, I go, and I ask the command, my immediate commander, can I go see, I'm not getting paid.

53:16.280 --> 53:24.740
He sends me over to the base payroll offices, and they look at their records, and they're panicky.

53:24.740 --> 53:35.600
You're on this base, and they send me back to weather school. I go back to weather school, and two MP air policemen and a dog come in and grab me

53:35.600 --> 53:39.080
and march me over to the base commander's office.

53:40.840 --> 53:43.940
I'm a little terrified, and the base commander says,

53:44.680 --> 53:49.440
Airman Hall, if you have a copy of your orders showing you that you're supposed to be on this base,

53:49.840 --> 53:56.320
then you're going to be a happy man, and whoever gave you the orders is not going to be very happy.

53:56.320 --> 54:02.480
But if you don't have a copy of the orders, the man who gave them to you is going to be a happy man,

54:02.480 --> 54:06.160
and you're not going to be a soldier. You're not going to be a very happy soldier,

54:06.160 --> 54:11.140
because the generals tell me you're too valuable a man to be wasted at this school.

54:11.900 --> 54:17.160
I had two copies in my hall. I said, thank you, Sergeant Matt, you're Sergeant Peoples.

54:17.440 --> 54:20.860
I graced his hand. I said, you need another one. I can copy this, right?

54:20.860 --> 54:26.500
I was a happy man. They said, well, we'll decide what to do, right?

54:26.980 --> 54:31.380
So they'd been looking for me at St. Angels, Texas for six weeks.

54:31.840 --> 54:34.380
The FBI had been looking for me at my house in London.

54:34.840 --> 54:38.320
Nobody had found me. I go back, and the sergeant comes out and says,

54:38.420 --> 54:40.220
You're going to Nellis, okay?

54:40.600 --> 54:40.980
Wow.

54:41.260 --> 54:46.000
Yeah. They gave me the usual wish list.

54:46.000 --> 54:50.180
When you finish weather school, name three places you'd like to go.

54:50.180 --> 54:56.220
I said, Germany, England, and March Air Force Base, Los Angeles.

54:56.360 --> 54:57.960
And I said, no, you're going to Nellis.

54:58.300 --> 55:03.580
How soon after you're stationed at Nellis do you encounter this abandoned weather station

55:03.580 --> 55:05.800
and meet your first tall white?

55:07.740 --> 55:14.240
Well, the first time that I heard tell of the tall whites at Nellis

55:14.240 --> 55:22.580
was that my very first duty session had Nellis with another airman,

55:22.780 --> 55:25.760
which I describe in my book, okay?

55:25.840 --> 55:29.320
He was the airman that had been on leave for several weeks

55:29.320 --> 55:34.340
because he claimed the Nellis weather station was haunted.

55:34.340 --> 55:37.660
And it's not the one you see there today.

55:38.140 --> 55:43.400
It was the old one that was the northeast end of the base operations building.

55:44.020 --> 55:47.580
The base operations building was a very nice building for its day,

55:47.700 --> 55:49.020
as was the weather station.

55:49.520 --> 55:51.140
I describe it in my book.

55:51.480 --> 55:53.740
And it had something very important.

55:53.860 --> 55:57.300
It was the military version of an airport terminal.

55:57.300 --> 56:00.180
And it had something very important.

56:00.840 --> 56:02.920
It had clean restrooms.

56:03.960 --> 56:09.420
The next clean restroom was a mile away in a group of barracks they were still building.

56:10.020 --> 56:14.180
To get to another clean restroom, you had to go a mile and a half away, okay?

56:14.520 --> 56:19.020
He claimed that when he was working NYCHA graveyard,

56:19.740 --> 56:24.520
and he had been in its military, he was on his fourth year,

56:24.520 --> 56:31.460
the previous swimmer that he thought ghosts,

56:31.940 --> 56:35.760
you and I would say a group of five tall white aliens,

56:35.980 --> 56:41.100
had come in off the runway, off the tarmac,

56:41.680 --> 56:47.140
unlocking the glass doors between the base operations,

56:47.260 --> 56:49.840
the interior of the base operations building, the tarmac,

56:50.160 --> 56:53.400
because one of the force fields will make every piece of material

56:53.400 --> 56:56.920
repel every other piece of material and just pop every lock open.

56:57.700 --> 57:02.740
And that when he came in, there was one waiting outside, standing guard,

57:02.880 --> 57:04.400
one holding the door open,

57:05.200 --> 57:08.300
and then that's two men,

57:08.700 --> 57:13.960
and then three women, one holding open the door to the bathroom,

57:14.640 --> 57:16.000
another one inside,

57:16.740 --> 57:19.200
helping them hold open the door to the bathroom,

57:19.200 --> 57:22.440
while the third one was using the ladies' restroom,

57:22.880 --> 57:25.640
and that they were rotating so that they'd come in to use the restroom.

57:26.180 --> 57:29.300
He didn't, he, although he described them doing that,

57:29.820 --> 57:32.220
he didn't appreciate what he was describing.

57:32.900 --> 57:34.240
He thought they were ghosts.

57:34.380 --> 57:36.880
He panicked immediately and started screaming,

57:37.400 --> 57:38.800
locked himself in the doorway,

57:38.800 --> 57:42.780
and called the base air police,

57:43.020 --> 57:46.540
only to discover that the Nellis base commander said,

57:46.680 --> 57:52.240
no, the air police cannot come beyond the road junction a mile away.

57:52.560 --> 57:53.660
He's on his own.

57:54.180 --> 57:54.340
Okay?

57:54.860 --> 57:58.460
Now, I know from firsthand experience that he was telling the truth,

57:58.920 --> 58:03.080
because there came a day when I had worked,

58:03.200 --> 58:04.220
I was working graveyard,

58:04.220 --> 58:07.940
actually a whole bunch of days on Sunday night when everything was empty,

58:08.520 --> 58:09.660
when that would happen.

58:10.020 --> 58:13.800
And the reason that they came is because they're just like us.

58:13.920 --> 58:16.860
The bathroom that was a mile down,

58:17.020 --> 58:20.700
which the mechanics down in that hangar,

58:20.780 --> 58:24.620
airport hangar, thought was haunted,

58:25.580 --> 58:29.260
was occasionally visited by tall white men

58:29.260 --> 58:30.780
who had to go to the bathroom,

58:31.340 --> 58:33.320
and it was a mess, never cleaned.

58:33.320 --> 58:36.980
And if you were out with two men and three women

58:36.980 --> 58:38.340
who wanted a clean bathroom,

58:38.920 --> 58:42.180
and the one a mile and a half down was too far

58:42.180 --> 58:43.220
and wasn't suitable,

58:43.820 --> 58:46.020
and you said, where do we want to go to the bathroom,

58:46.140 --> 58:47.700
you'd say, I know just the place.

58:48.100 --> 58:49.380
It's the one in the base ops,

58:49.420 --> 58:51.380
and on Sunday night there's nobody around.

58:51.900 --> 58:52.960
There's the weather observer,

58:53.060 --> 58:56.080
and he's usually sleeping at night like he should.

58:56.560 --> 58:56.960
Okay?

58:57.080 --> 58:59.720
He's not supposed to, but usually they did.

59:00.220 --> 59:01.840
Actually, that was a great place to sleep.

59:01.840 --> 59:05.740
I myself didn't, but I had too much fun reading books and stuff.

59:06.440 --> 59:11.160
And so, and the guy that I was, he was my OJT instructor,

59:11.260 --> 59:14.220
he also claimed that on a different night when he was in there,

59:14.300 --> 59:16.900
that one of them came and peeked at him around the corner

59:16.900 --> 59:19.400
and said, don't worry, the women just want to use the restroom.

59:19.980 --> 59:22.740
He screamed and called the police again,

59:22.780 --> 59:23.560
and they wouldn't come,

59:23.560 --> 59:25.320
and he had a nervous breakdown.

59:25.560 --> 59:27.360
So, you know, and that happened to me.

59:27.780 --> 59:31.340
I said, yeah, don't forget the candy bar machine.

59:31.480 --> 59:32.620
You know, you guys may be hungry.

59:33.160 --> 59:33.460
Right?

59:33.520 --> 59:36.960
And that's what psychological defenses do for you, you see?

59:37.020 --> 59:37.900
That's the difference.

59:37.900 --> 59:40.640
And, and, and, but that's the first one.

59:41.060 --> 59:43.240
I, the, I, he told me the story,

59:43.380 --> 59:48.280
but I didn't actually see the tall whites on that night.

59:48.520 --> 59:50.760
Then a few nights later,

59:50.760 --> 59:54.460
when he had been given an honorable discharge,

59:54.460 --> 59:59.080
because the Pentagon insisted that he and I alone in the warehouse,

59:59.080 --> 01:00:02.280
on Sunday night, alone in the weather station,

01:00:02.280 --> 01:00:06.440
and together work at least one duty shift,

01:00:06.720 --> 01:00:09.300
and then he would be given an honorable discharge,

01:00:09.380 --> 01:00:11.000
a section eight, which he was.

01:00:11.440 --> 01:00:14.580
Then when I was with my next duty shift,

01:00:15.240 --> 01:00:16.920
my next OJT instructor,

01:00:17.420 --> 01:00:19.400
and he was working a double shift,

01:00:19.880 --> 01:00:21.600
I was working swing shift.

01:00:21.900 --> 01:00:25.140
When I came left at midnight,

01:00:25.140 --> 01:00:28.060
and I was trying to hurry to get to the base up,

01:00:28.160 --> 01:00:29.440
to the base chow hall,

01:00:29.440 --> 01:00:33.660
as I was walking back the mile or so to my barracks,

01:00:34.060 --> 01:00:35.640
one of the new ones being built,

01:00:36.380 --> 01:00:39.120
I would, and I, when I turned around,

01:00:40.160 --> 01:00:43.420
following me was the tall white girl,

01:00:43.780 --> 01:00:45.120
that, the 12-year-old,

01:00:45.960 --> 01:00:48.420
and I was about a quarter mile down from the,

01:00:48.820 --> 01:00:50.440
base up from the weather station,

01:00:50.680 --> 01:00:54.720
and back by the white elephant was the teacher,

01:00:54.720 --> 01:00:58.000
and two, Ridge for Harry,

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:00.740
and another tall white guard,

01:01:01.380 --> 01:01:03.580
happily watching me from a distance,

01:01:03.700 --> 01:01:06.540
and all she was doing was just following me,

01:01:07.180 --> 01:01:09.560
intentionally showing herself.

01:01:10.160 --> 01:01:12.400
At the time, I,

01:01:12.780 --> 01:01:15.600
when you talk about what good are psychological defenses,

01:01:15.740 --> 01:01:18.540
at the time, I couldn't believe my eyes,

01:01:18.600 --> 01:01:21.640
even though they matched what the guy had told me

01:01:21.640 --> 01:01:22.760
just a few days before.

01:01:22.760 --> 01:01:25.560
I decided that because I was tired,

01:01:26.140 --> 01:01:27.920
I must be sleepwalking.

01:01:28.480 --> 01:01:31.420
And I said, well, gee, I thought if you slept,

01:01:31.520 --> 01:01:33.960
I didn't realize that you could actually walk

01:01:33.960 --> 01:01:35.680
and see things when you were sleepwalking.

01:01:36.100 --> 01:01:37.740
And so I turned,

01:01:37.860 --> 01:01:39.680
and I tried to continue walking.

01:01:39.800 --> 01:01:41.940
I expected to hurry and get to my barracks

01:01:41.940 --> 01:01:45.940
before I had a brain stroke or something and collapsed.

01:01:45.940 --> 01:01:48.200
And I thought, and I turned around,

01:01:48.780 --> 01:01:51.540
and after going a few steps,

01:01:51.580 --> 01:01:53.300
and there she was, she still followed me.

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:56.280
And I had been reading a book on the Titanic,

01:01:56.900 --> 01:01:58.440
which I can talk about later.

01:01:59.180 --> 01:02:00.480
And in the Titanic,

01:02:00.600 --> 01:02:02.420
it described a group of angels

01:02:02.420 --> 01:02:03.980
who came in a craft,

01:02:04.560 --> 01:02:06.180
land one of the lifeboats,

01:02:06.320 --> 01:02:09.260
and landed on the ledge of one of the icebergs,

01:02:09.260 --> 01:02:11.320
and dropped wreaths

01:02:11.320 --> 01:02:14.380
for people in the water to use as life preservers,

01:02:14.460 --> 01:02:15.420
which didn't work.

01:02:16.200 --> 01:02:20.120
And how one of the angels was good at

01:02:20.120 --> 01:02:22.120
floating out over the water

01:02:22.120 --> 01:02:23.480
and dropping her hand.

01:02:24.060 --> 01:02:25.380
And when I turned around,

01:02:25.460 --> 01:02:26.740
and I was just watching her,

01:02:26.840 --> 01:02:27.680
she smiled.

01:02:28.220 --> 01:02:28.800
That girl,

01:02:29.340 --> 01:02:30.240
she lifted up,

01:02:30.760 --> 01:02:33.900
turned up the power on her suit,

01:02:34.040 --> 01:02:35.600
lifted up a little bit further

01:02:35.600 --> 01:02:37.440
till the top of her feet

01:02:37.440 --> 01:02:39.520
were about as far off the ground

01:02:39.520 --> 01:02:40.620
as the top,

01:02:40.760 --> 01:02:41.480
not as top,

01:02:41.760 --> 01:02:43.540
almost the top of that chair,

01:02:44.020 --> 01:02:47.080
flew over beside the sidewalk,

01:02:47.880 --> 01:02:49.820
which was over the grass,

01:02:50.820 --> 01:02:52.660
and saw,

01:02:52.980 --> 01:02:54.880
and went over the grass a little bit,

01:02:55.560 --> 01:02:57.480
and saw on the grass

01:02:57.480 --> 01:02:58.600
something that,

01:02:59.800 --> 01:03:01.780
a piece of wrapper,

01:03:02.040 --> 01:03:03.880
or perhaps a quarter or something

01:03:03.880 --> 01:03:04.880
that interested her.

01:03:05.380 --> 01:03:07.400
And with her feet still in the air,

01:03:07.400 --> 01:03:10.360
lowered her shoulders,

01:03:11.080 --> 01:03:12.260
reached down on the grass,

01:03:12.360 --> 01:03:13.320
and picked it up,

01:03:13.880 --> 01:03:16.740
assuming the very same position

01:03:16.740 --> 01:03:19.640
that was described in the book

01:03:19.640 --> 01:03:20.600
on the Titanic

01:03:20.600 --> 01:03:23.340
that I had previously read,

01:03:23.380 --> 01:03:25.440
like that night or two nights before,

01:03:26.160 --> 01:03:27.800
described by the lady

01:03:27.800 --> 01:03:30.080
in the Survivor of the Lifeboat

01:03:30.080 --> 01:03:32.720
that was picked up by the Carpathia

01:03:32.720 --> 01:03:34.600
as described in the book

01:03:34.600 --> 01:03:35.640
that I was reading.

01:03:35.640 --> 01:03:37.680
And it was like,

01:03:37.740 --> 01:03:39.240
she was the very same girl,

01:03:39.360 --> 01:03:40.140
and considering that

01:03:40.140 --> 01:03:41.160
the 12 whites live

01:03:41.160 --> 01:03:42.520
600, 800 years,

01:03:42.600 --> 01:03:43.780
10 times longer than we do,

01:03:44.280 --> 01:03:45.640
she could have been.

01:03:46.100 --> 01:03:46.260
Okay?

01:03:46.620 --> 01:03:48.180
And when I looked at it,

01:03:48.840 --> 01:03:49.860
I was stunned.

01:03:50.260 --> 01:03:51.620
And I still didn't make

01:03:51.620 --> 01:03:52.780
the association

01:03:52.780 --> 01:03:55.840
between those people

01:03:55.840 --> 01:03:56.640
an extraterrestrials.

01:03:57.720 --> 01:03:59.740
That's what psychological defenses

01:03:59.740 --> 01:04:00.540
do for you.

01:04:00.540 --> 01:04:01.720
And I decided

01:04:01.720 --> 01:04:03.160
that I must just be

01:04:03.160 --> 01:04:04.680
sleepwalking

01:04:04.680 --> 01:04:05.820
or there must be something

01:04:05.820 --> 01:04:06.560
with me mentally.

01:04:06.680 --> 01:04:07.460
And I went home

01:04:07.460 --> 01:04:09.460
and I went back to my barracks

01:04:09.460 --> 01:04:15.740
and life continued.

01:04:16.260 --> 01:04:17.760
So, let's get into

01:04:17.760 --> 01:04:19.140
the Hall-Photon theory

01:04:19.140 --> 01:04:19.620
because,

01:04:20.020 --> 01:04:20.860
and just to set this up

01:04:20.860 --> 01:04:21.440
for the audience,

01:04:21.900 --> 01:04:22.860
also in the 30s,

01:04:22.880 --> 01:04:23.760
in 1935,

01:04:24.260 --> 01:04:25.760
Einstein, Rosen, Podolsky

01:04:25.760 --> 01:04:26.760
come up with their

01:04:26.760 --> 01:04:27.880
sort of spooky action

01:04:27.880 --> 01:04:28.700
at a distance,

01:04:28.700 --> 01:04:29.940
entanglement.

01:04:30.220 --> 01:04:30.880
And it's known

01:04:30.880 --> 01:04:31.880
as Einstein's dilemma

01:04:31.880 --> 01:04:32.920
because Einstein

01:04:32.920 --> 01:04:34.400
had always kind of

01:04:34.400 --> 01:04:35.280
almost put a governor

01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:35.940
on reality.

01:04:36.080 --> 01:04:37.340
The speed limit of reality

01:04:37.340 --> 01:04:38.800
is the, you know,

01:04:38.820 --> 01:04:39.480
speed of light.

01:04:40.140 --> 01:04:40.960
And yet,

01:04:41.300 --> 01:04:42.180
with photons,

01:04:42.360 --> 01:04:42.860
observably,

01:04:42.980 --> 01:04:43.800
you see this sort of

01:04:43.800 --> 01:04:44.680
entanglement effect

01:04:44.680 --> 01:04:46.100
where optical properties,

01:04:46.300 --> 01:04:47.360
various optical properties,

01:04:47.540 --> 01:04:49.520
seem to mirror one another

01:04:49.520 --> 01:04:50.940
at vast distances

01:04:50.940 --> 01:04:52.280
just instantaneously.

01:04:53.060 --> 01:04:53.580
And so,

01:04:53.700 --> 01:04:55.940
how is the Hall-Photon theory

01:04:55.940 --> 01:04:57.080
an update on that?

01:04:57.480 --> 01:04:58.680
And how does that unlock?

01:04:59.060 --> 01:05:00.400
Faster-than-light travel

01:05:00.400 --> 01:05:01.860
in the form of a spacecraft?

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:03.780
Well, to begin with,

01:05:03.820 --> 01:05:04.720
I'd like to thank you

01:05:04.720 --> 01:05:05.820
for this nice interview.

01:05:06.140 --> 01:05:07.580
And if I don't,

01:05:07.900 --> 01:05:10.240
and having us on your podcast,

01:05:10.620 --> 01:05:12.860
I'd like to congratulate you

01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:14.460
on just out thinking Einstein.

01:05:15.740 --> 01:05:16.600
When you say,

01:05:16.680 --> 01:05:17.500
what's it feel like

01:05:17.500 --> 01:05:19.060
to be smarter than Albert Einstein?

01:05:19.420 --> 01:05:20.520
I say, well,

01:05:20.820 --> 01:05:21.660
I know a guy.

01:05:21.960 --> 01:05:23.240
It's not just me

01:05:23.240 --> 01:05:24.240
because what you say

01:05:24.240 --> 01:05:24.940
is correct.

01:05:25.900 --> 01:05:27.340
And the easiest way

01:05:27.340 --> 01:05:28.100
to see it

01:05:28.100 --> 01:05:29.900
is starting with

01:05:29.900 --> 01:05:30.800
the way Einstein did

01:05:30.800 --> 01:05:32.020
with the Mickelson-Morley

01:05:32.020 --> 01:05:33.840
experiment of 1897.

01:05:33.920 --> 01:05:34.040
Yeah.

01:05:34.300 --> 01:05:34.640
Okay?

01:05:35.400 --> 01:05:36.040
In 1890,

01:05:36.260 --> 01:05:37.160
which was a failure.

01:05:37.340 --> 01:05:37.620
Yes.

01:05:37.620 --> 01:05:39.020
In 1897,

01:05:39.020 --> 01:05:40.100
everyone thought

01:05:40.100 --> 01:05:41.820
that a photon of light

01:05:41.820 --> 01:05:44.860
had only two force fields,

01:05:44.960 --> 01:05:45.960
an electric field

01:05:45.960 --> 01:05:47.080
and a magnetic field

01:05:47.080 --> 01:05:49.060
that oscillated together.

01:05:49.400 --> 01:05:49.640
Okay?

01:05:49.640 --> 01:05:51.920
They ran perpendicular

01:05:51.920 --> 01:05:52.500
to one another.

01:05:52.620 --> 01:05:52.820
Mm-hmm.

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:53.280
Mm-hmm.

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:55.080
And then they did

01:05:55.080 --> 01:05:57.080
the Mickelson-Morley experiment.

01:05:57.640 --> 01:05:58.700
And then they wanted

01:05:58.700 --> 01:06:00.100
to interpret it

01:06:00.100 --> 01:06:01.700
as though it were

01:06:01.700 --> 01:06:02.760
an experiment

01:06:02.760 --> 01:06:03.560
that you would do

01:06:03.560 --> 01:06:05.140
with little boats

01:06:05.140 --> 01:06:06.260
crossing a river

01:06:06.260 --> 01:06:07.480
and going up and down

01:06:07.480 --> 01:06:08.020
in the river

01:06:08.020 --> 01:06:09.760
when they didn't know

01:06:09.760 --> 01:06:11.060
anything about the photon.

01:06:11.100 --> 01:06:11.840
They thought they knew

01:06:11.840 --> 01:06:12.520
everything there was

01:06:12.520 --> 01:06:13.420
to know about the photon,

01:06:13.680 --> 01:06:14.300
that there was only

01:06:14.300 --> 01:06:15.260
two force fields,

01:06:15.480 --> 01:06:16.920
so they could pretend

01:06:16.920 --> 01:06:17.920
that they knew

01:06:17.920 --> 01:06:19.640
everything about

01:06:19.640 --> 01:06:20.580
how a photon

01:06:20.580 --> 01:06:21.880
looks like a little boat

01:06:21.880 --> 01:06:23.140
going across the river.

01:06:23.600 --> 01:06:23.660
Okay?

01:06:24.340 --> 01:06:26.220
When the experiment failed,

01:06:26.360 --> 01:06:27.440
then nobody wanted

01:06:27.440 --> 01:06:28.300
to say

01:06:28.300 --> 01:06:29.720
there has to be

01:06:29.720 --> 01:06:30.680
more structure

01:06:30.680 --> 01:06:31.620
to the photon

01:06:31.620 --> 01:06:33.700
than what we know about.

01:06:34.140 --> 01:06:34.820
Nobody wanted

01:06:34.820 --> 01:06:35.560
to do that.

01:06:35.640 --> 01:06:35.980
Okay?

01:06:36.740 --> 01:06:36.920
They,

01:06:36.920 --> 01:06:38.240
James Clerk Maxwell

01:06:38.240 --> 01:06:40.080
had done his equations

01:06:40.080 --> 01:06:40.900
and they didn't want

01:06:40.900 --> 01:06:41.400
to say

01:06:41.400 --> 01:06:43.140
there's more force fields

01:06:43.140 --> 01:06:44.520
that Maxwell's equations

01:06:44.520 --> 01:06:45.680
don't include

01:06:45.680 --> 01:06:46.600
but should.

01:06:46.920 --> 01:06:47.720
Okay?

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:50.400
And they oscillate too.

01:06:50.620 --> 01:06:51.600
They wanted to say

01:06:51.600 --> 01:06:52.720
we know everything

01:06:52.720 --> 01:06:53.420
there is to know

01:06:53.420 --> 01:06:54.180
about the photon.

01:06:54.900 --> 01:06:55.960
And then they wanted

01:06:55.960 --> 01:06:56.460
to say

01:06:56.460 --> 01:06:57.340
and we know everything

01:06:57.340 --> 01:06:58.200
about the river

01:06:58.200 --> 01:06:58.960
and the banks

01:06:58.960 --> 01:06:59.540
and stuff

01:06:59.540 --> 01:07:00.280
and the little boats

01:07:00.280 --> 01:07:01.160
that cross it.

01:07:01.720 --> 01:07:03.120
So now they'd reasoned

01:07:03.120 --> 01:07:04.660
themselves into a corner,

01:07:04.880 --> 01:07:05.360
so what did

01:07:05.360 --> 01:07:06.400
the experiment fail?

01:07:07.120 --> 01:07:07.820
And they monkeyed

01:07:07.820 --> 01:07:08.560
around like that

01:07:08.560 --> 01:07:09.440
until Einstein

01:07:09.440 --> 01:07:10.420
and they finally

01:07:10.420 --> 01:07:11.360
asked Einstein

01:07:11.360 --> 01:07:12.080
But I think of it

01:07:12.080 --> 01:07:12.600
as a failure

01:07:12.600 --> 01:07:13.720
to detect the ether,

01:07:14.160 --> 01:07:14.940
the Michelson-Morley

01:07:14.940 --> 01:07:15.680
experiments.

01:07:15.800 --> 01:07:16.240
Is that right?

01:07:16.240 --> 01:07:16.580
To think

01:07:16.580 --> 01:07:17.800
a medium

01:07:17.800 --> 01:07:18.640
through which

01:07:18.640 --> 01:07:19.740
the photons

01:07:19.740 --> 01:07:20.380
would be carried.

01:07:20.500 --> 01:07:21.580
That would make sense,

01:07:21.720 --> 01:07:22.000
yeah,

01:07:22.200 --> 01:07:23.560
that there was no ether

01:07:23.560 --> 01:07:24.680
but then that left

01:07:24.680 --> 01:07:25.280
the question,

01:07:26.080 --> 01:07:27.860
so why isn't there

01:07:27.860 --> 01:07:29.240
at least some change,

01:07:29.340 --> 01:07:30.220
why did the experiment

01:07:30.220 --> 01:07:31.660
totally fail?

01:07:32.160 --> 01:07:32.320
Okay?

01:07:32.700 --> 01:07:33.600
Along the way

01:07:33.600 --> 01:07:34.740
they ignored things

01:07:34.740 --> 01:07:36.000
about the experiment.

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:38.200
the first one is that

01:07:38.200 --> 01:07:39.860
if you do the experiment

01:07:39.860 --> 01:07:41.360
with one photon

01:07:41.360 --> 01:07:42.700
at a time

01:07:42.700 --> 01:07:44.460
in the interferometer,

01:07:44.900 --> 01:07:46.760
you get the same results

01:07:46.760 --> 01:07:48.440
and that means

01:07:48.440 --> 01:07:49.080
that the photon

01:07:49.080 --> 01:07:50.940
has to be split in two

01:07:50.940 --> 01:07:52.760
for that to work.

01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:54.520
Today we call that

01:07:54.520 --> 01:07:55.960
photon entanglement,

01:07:56.480 --> 01:07:57.720
but back then

01:07:57.720 --> 01:07:58.280
they said,

01:07:58.560 --> 01:07:58.740
well,

01:07:58.740 --> 01:07:59.060
I don't know,

01:07:59.560 --> 01:08:00.580
spook you at a distance,

01:08:00.660 --> 01:08:00.840
right?

01:08:00.840 --> 01:08:02.840
And then if you do it

01:08:02.840 --> 01:08:04.180
with photons

01:08:04.180 --> 01:08:06.460
of just red light,

01:08:07.040 --> 01:08:08.440
then you get

01:08:08.440 --> 01:08:09.800
the same results,

01:08:10.320 --> 01:08:13.320
but the bright bands

01:08:13.320 --> 01:08:14.240
of light

01:08:14.240 --> 01:08:16.900
are still red light.

01:08:17.680 --> 01:08:18.700
And so therefore,

01:08:19.060 --> 01:08:20.240
the explanation

01:08:20.240 --> 01:08:22.340
that the photons

01:08:22.340 --> 01:08:25.040
would constructively interfere

01:08:25.040 --> 01:08:26.480
and destructively interfere

01:08:26.480 --> 01:08:28.400
can't be correct

01:08:28.400 --> 01:08:30.320
because if they

01:08:30.320 --> 01:08:32.460
constructively interfered,

01:08:32.500 --> 01:08:33.100
they would have

01:08:33.100 --> 01:08:34.340
to change color.

01:08:35.220 --> 01:08:36.040
Blue photons

01:08:36.040 --> 01:08:37.260
have twice the energy

01:08:37.260 --> 01:08:38.400
of red photons,

01:08:38.620 --> 01:08:39.660
so that would mean

01:08:39.660 --> 01:08:40.460
you would be sending

01:08:40.460 --> 01:08:41.840
in blue light

01:08:41.840 --> 01:08:43.660
or sending in red light

01:08:43.660 --> 01:08:44.880
and looking at

01:08:44.880 --> 01:08:46.200
interference patterns

01:08:46.200 --> 01:08:47.180
of red light,

01:08:47.300 --> 01:08:48.680
but that's not the case.

01:08:49.280 --> 01:08:50.420
All that's happening

01:08:50.420 --> 01:08:51.860
in the interferometer

01:08:51.860 --> 01:08:53.840
is that the photons

01:08:53.840 --> 01:08:55.620
are being steered

01:08:55.620 --> 01:08:57.820
into bands

01:08:57.820 --> 01:08:59.100
of red photons

01:08:59.100 --> 01:09:00.640
that needs

01:09:00.640 --> 01:09:01.800
another force field

01:09:01.800 --> 01:09:02.800
to do the steering.

01:09:03.320 --> 01:09:03.780
So what is,

01:09:03.900 --> 01:09:04.340
if you have,

01:09:04.660 --> 01:09:05.620
in traditional

01:09:05.620 --> 01:09:07.000
electromagnetism,

01:09:07.120 --> 01:09:08.260
classical electrodynamics,

01:09:08.320 --> 01:09:08.660
you have

01:09:08.660 --> 01:09:10.900
an electric field,

01:09:10.960 --> 01:09:11.840
a magnetic field,

01:09:12.060 --> 01:09:12.900
and a wave,

01:09:13.100 --> 01:09:13.880
and they're all sort of

01:09:13.880 --> 01:09:14.480
running perpendicular

01:09:14.480 --> 01:09:15.160
to one another,

01:09:15.260 --> 01:09:16.560
what other field types

01:09:16.560 --> 01:09:17.780
do you think exist

01:09:17.780 --> 01:09:19.120
in the whole photon theory?

01:09:20.600 --> 01:09:21.760
A whole bunch.

01:09:22.360 --> 01:09:22.680
Okay.

01:09:22.860 --> 01:09:23.320
Like what?

01:09:23.640 --> 01:09:24.060
Okay.

01:09:24.060 --> 01:09:26.020
And remember,

01:09:26.180 --> 01:09:27.420
the force fields

01:09:27.420 --> 01:09:28.500
can be different

01:09:28.500 --> 01:09:30.200
force strengths.

01:09:31.220 --> 01:09:33.380
The electric force,

01:09:33.600 --> 01:09:34.840
magnetic force field,

01:09:35.440 --> 01:09:36.240
is considered

01:09:36.240 --> 01:09:37.520
pound for pound

01:09:37.520 --> 01:09:39.320
to be like,

01:09:39.420 --> 01:09:39.800
what,

01:09:39.860 --> 01:09:40.980
a trillion times,

01:09:41.540 --> 01:09:42.860
I might not have

01:09:42.860 --> 01:09:43.660
that number right,

01:09:44.340 --> 01:09:45.860
a hundred million times

01:09:45.860 --> 01:09:47.140
more powerful

01:09:47.140 --> 01:09:48.120
pound for pound

01:09:48.120 --> 01:09:49.360
than the force of gravity.

01:09:49.540 --> 01:09:49.720
Yeah,

01:09:49.800 --> 01:09:50.800
it's 10 to the 40th.

01:09:50.800 --> 01:09:52.240
But because the force

01:09:52.240 --> 01:09:53.580
of gravity is weaker

01:09:53.580 --> 01:09:55.360
pound for pound

01:09:55.360 --> 01:09:56.800
than the electromagnetic field,

01:09:57.160 --> 01:09:58.300
the force of gravity

01:09:58.300 --> 01:09:59.500
can move further

01:09:59.500 --> 01:10:00.640
than light.

01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:01.080
Okay?

01:10:01.480 --> 01:10:02.860
So the force of gravity

01:10:02.860 --> 01:10:03.780
from our galaxy

01:10:03.780 --> 01:10:04.420
can affect

01:10:04.420 --> 01:10:05.540
the nearby galaxy,

01:10:06.200 --> 01:10:07.200
the Andromeda galaxy,

01:10:07.320 --> 01:10:09.260
at 2.7 million light years,

01:10:09.720 --> 01:10:11.560
whereas the force of electricity

01:10:11.560 --> 01:10:12.820
from our galaxy

01:10:12.820 --> 01:10:13.260
cannot.

01:10:13.260 --> 01:10:13.780
Right?

01:10:13.780 --> 01:10:14.100
Right?

01:10:15.500 --> 01:10:17.020
But Einstein wanted

01:10:17.020 --> 01:10:18.640
to ruin that analogy

01:10:18.640 --> 01:10:19.420
by saying,

01:10:19.900 --> 01:10:21.860
to protect his own reputation,

01:10:22.060 --> 01:10:22.420
I guess,

01:10:22.500 --> 01:10:23.740
I have no idea why,

01:10:24.680 --> 01:10:25.800
trying to say

01:10:25.800 --> 01:10:26.840
that nothing could travel

01:10:26.840 --> 01:10:27.840
faster than light,

01:10:27.920 --> 01:10:28.860
not even gravity.

01:10:28.860 --> 01:10:30.740
But obviously,

01:10:30.920 --> 01:10:31.920
if gravity can travel

01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:32.800
further than light,

01:10:32.860 --> 01:10:33.860
it must be traveling

01:10:33.860 --> 01:10:35.440
faster than light.

01:10:35.800 --> 01:10:38.280
If you look at the symmetry

01:10:38.280 --> 01:10:39.920
of the Andromeda galaxy,

01:10:40.900 --> 01:10:41.940
and you say,

01:10:42.040 --> 01:10:42.300
well,

01:10:42.680 --> 01:10:43.560
it's,

01:10:43.820 --> 01:10:44.040
what,

01:10:44.220 --> 01:10:45.160
10,000,

01:10:45.400 --> 01:10:46.680
100,000 light years,

01:10:46.820 --> 01:10:47.760
200,000 light years

01:10:47.760 --> 01:10:48.480
across,

01:10:48.660 --> 01:10:51.020
and that means that,

01:10:51.020 --> 01:10:53.700
and it's so well organized,

01:10:54.980 --> 01:10:57.100
gravity must be traveling

01:10:57.100 --> 01:10:58.600
trillions of times

01:10:58.600 --> 01:10:59.920
faster than light.

01:11:00.360 --> 01:11:00.840
Otherwise,

01:11:01.720 --> 01:11:03.220
if the stars

01:11:03.220 --> 01:11:04.460
were trying to do that,

01:11:04.520 --> 01:11:06.100
and gravity was only

01:11:06.100 --> 01:11:07.140
traveling at the speed

01:11:07.140 --> 01:11:07.580
of light,

01:11:08.060 --> 01:11:08.660
they'd all bump

01:11:08.660 --> 01:11:09.440
into each other.

01:11:09.800 --> 01:11:10.100
Why do you,

01:11:10.300 --> 01:11:10.500
so,

01:11:11.060 --> 01:11:12.300
is gravity in your model

01:11:12.300 --> 01:11:14.160
also orders of magnitude

01:11:14.160 --> 01:11:15.740
weaker than electromagnetism?

01:11:15.820 --> 01:11:16.940
Because if it's traveling

01:11:16.940 --> 01:11:17.980
that far,

01:11:17.980 --> 01:11:18.880
and having an effect,

01:11:19.020 --> 01:11:19.660
a pulling effect

01:11:19.660 --> 01:11:21.220
between mass bodies?

01:11:21.860 --> 01:11:22.500
If it's weaker,

01:11:22.700 --> 01:11:23.720
then it could go further.

01:11:24.440 --> 01:11:25.380
And see,

01:11:25.620 --> 01:11:26.520
in the photon,

01:11:26.520 --> 01:11:27.680
How does that hold?

01:11:27.760 --> 01:11:28.240
If it's weaker,

01:11:28.360 --> 01:11:28.920
it goes further?

01:11:30.080 --> 01:11:31.540
Because it's like,

01:11:31.560 --> 01:11:33.580
it's like the milk truck

01:11:33.580 --> 01:11:34.480
delivering milk,

01:11:34.580 --> 01:11:34.900
right?

01:11:35.380 --> 01:11:36.340
If it's going to go down

01:11:36.340 --> 01:11:37.000
the street and hit

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:37.580
every house,

01:11:37.640 --> 01:11:38.500
and it's going to stop

01:11:38.500 --> 01:11:40.120
and interact along the way,

01:11:40.240 --> 01:11:41.900
or at least stand ready to.

01:11:42.480 --> 01:11:43.660
But if it's going to

01:11:43.660 --> 01:11:45.440
just do one house here

01:11:45.440 --> 01:11:46.940
and a house 10 miles down,

01:11:47.320 --> 01:11:48.120
the guy can go

01:11:48.120 --> 01:11:48.860
into high gear.

01:11:49.200 --> 01:11:49.800
But I would think of,

01:11:49.920 --> 01:11:50.140
like,

01:11:50.520 --> 01:11:52.080
attenuation as being,

01:11:52.220 --> 01:11:52.460
you know,

01:11:52.540 --> 01:11:54.100
like a wave being,

01:11:54.280 --> 01:11:54.460
you know,

01:11:54.520 --> 01:11:55.260
a certain kind of strength,

01:11:55.260 --> 01:11:56.200
and then it attenuates.

01:11:56.900 --> 01:11:57.980
The only way

01:11:57.980 --> 01:11:59.200
a force field

01:11:59.200 --> 01:12:00.200
can attenuate

01:12:00.200 --> 01:12:01.880
is there,

01:12:02.520 --> 01:12:03.120
say like,

01:12:03.220 --> 01:12:06.020
I'll say like gravity,

01:12:06.320 --> 01:12:08.720
is for there to be

01:12:08.720 --> 01:12:10.880
an interaction cross-section

01:12:10.880 --> 01:12:13.580
put up by another piece

01:12:13.580 --> 01:12:15.040
of matter

01:12:15.040 --> 01:12:16.720
or energy

